The paper deals with the fundamental trade-off among identification, secrecy, template, and privacy-leakage rates in a biometric identification system. This involves the use of information theory and cryptography, which are typically covered in the cs.IT and cs.CR sub-categories. The paper also involves the processing of biometric data, which falls under the cs.MM and cs.CV sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses a novel technique to prove the capacity region of the rate tuples, which could be of interest to researchers in the cs.LG sub-category.
